CREATE2 allows hardware wallets and (light)clients to verify if a contract is secure or not without needing to know anything about Ethereum's current state. 

This is a small piece of what deterministic contract creation allows and we should move towards this as soon as possible.
nick.eth
@nicksdjohnson
 · Feb 22, 2019
Replying to @maurelian_ @danfinlay and 3 others
Actually, CREATE2 can *improve* the situation here, because it commits to the init code and the creator. That means you can verify entirely offline if the init code (and hence the deployed code) is "safe", something you can't do with CREATE.
